"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-20-paris-2024-super-falcons-tipped-for-olympics-medal\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Secretary General of the Nigeria Olympics Committee, NOC, Tunji Popoola has predicted a podium finish for the Super Falcons at the 2024 Olympic Games.  The Super Falcons are making a return to the Olympics since the 2008 edition in Beijing.  Randy Waldrum's side are drawn in a tough group with Spain, Japan and Brazil.  Popoola is, however, rooting for the nine-time African champions to win a medal in Paris.  \\\"We have a strong football team, I will tip them for a medal,\\\" he declared.  \\\"Also we should expect medals in athletics, weightlifting and wrestling.  \\\"We will surprise Nigerians with a bag of medals.\\\"  Transfer: I am not pushing Man Utd to sign De Ligt - Ten Hag gives update  Transfer: Chelsea, Napoli in talks over Osimhen's replacement, Lukaku  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"